text: "A male patient presents with sensory loss and weakness of limbs for 3 months. He also has angular stomatitis. On examination, there is loss of proprioception, vibration sensations, UMN type of lower limb weakness, and absent ankle reflex. What is the most probable diagnosis?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Extradural cord compression", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Multiple sclerosis", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Subacute combined degeneration of the cord", "is_correct": true}],
explanation: "$1a",
images: []
