tags: ["ZVRecommended", "PYQ", "INI-CET May 2025"],
text: "Which of the following brain regions is primarily associated with the processing of explicit memory?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Hippocampus", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "B", "text": "Amygdala", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Insular cortex", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Cerebellum", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "| **Type** | **Example** | **Brain Region** |\n| ---- | ------- | ------------ |\n| Explicit | Facts, events | Hippocampus |\n| Implicit (procedural) | Skills | Cerebellum, basal ganglia |<br><br>**Declarative / Explicit Memory:**<br><br>* **Semantic (factual):**\n    * Prefrontal cortex\n    * Temporal cortex (lateral and anterior)\n* **Episodic (events):**\n    * Hippocampus\n    * Medial temporal lobe\n    * Neocortex<br><br>**Nondeclarative / Implicit Memory:**<br><br>* **Procedural (skills, habits):**\n    * Striatum\n    * Cerebellum\n    * Motor cortex\n* **Priming and perceptual:**\n    * Neocortex\n* **Associative learning (classical conditioning):**\n    * Amygdala\n    * Cerebellum",
images: []
